<h2>How long have you been cycling in London?</h2>
<p>Since I moved here last year in August.</p>
<h2>What got you into cycling?</h2>
<p>I cycled a lot before moving to London, thought it a good habit and wanted to stick to it.</p>
<h2>Why do you ride a bike?</h2>
<p>Cycling makes me arrive fully energised at work - bye bye grumpy mornings. I also enjoy not being crammed in the morning tube. And you'd be surprised how often travelling by bicycle is faster than by public transport.</p>
<h2>Where do you cycle?</h2>
<p>I live in the North West of London, and I'd say that my cycle area is roughly bordered by the Barbican on the east side, Hampstead Heath in the north, Westminster in the south and Notting Hill in the west. But whenever Citymapper tells me I can be faster by bicycle than by public transport, and/or whenever the sun is out, I jump on my bike.</p>
</div>
 <div class="clearfix">
    <div class="image-box">
    
        
        
